scSensitiveGene_Manual

Zechuan Chen

2021/3/5

R package install

Before install scSensitiveGeneDefine, please install the Seurat,DoubletFinder,entropy and dplyr.

devtools::install_github("Zechuan-Chen/scSensitiveGeneDefine")
library(scSensitiveGeneDefine)

Data download

  1. You can get the common data from the https://support.10xgenomics.com/single-cell-gene-expression/datasets/
  2. The function runSeurat can be used to deal with the raw data, which can be download from the above link.
object<-runSeurat(data.dir="~/outs/filtered_feature_bc_matrix/",
                       sample_name = "scRNA-seq Sample 1",
                       PC = 40,
                       resolution = 0.6,
                       mt.cut_off = 20,
                       min_nFeature.cut_off = 200,
                       data_type = "Expression_matrix",
                       filter_doublet = T,
                       algorithm = 1)

High variable genes statistic

  1. Statistics on high variable genes of each subclusters
  2. The result will be used for sensitive genes defination.
  3. The example data PBMC can be load by data(PBMC). The example data can be get from the 10x Genomics Support
library(Seurat)
library(scSensitiveGeneDefine)
data(PBMC)
Idents(PBMC)<-"RNA_snn_res.0.6"

## Remove sensitive genes from variable Features 1. Only removing the sensitive genes from the variable features, not transcriptome. In this way, the unsupervised clustering result will be improved with transcript no change. 2. Some red points transform to be the black points. These points represent the sensitive genes in this data.

PBMC<-ReSelectVariableFeatures(PBMC,SensitiveGene = SensitiveGene)
VariableFeaturePlot(PBMC)
## Warning: Transformation introduced infinite values in continuous x-axis
